strain_description: ADE2-CAN1 inserted into rDNA array to measure frequency of rDNA recombination. From Kurt Runge.
strain_notes: This strain is the result of crossing the original assay strain (CCFY100 address 433418 with no associated genotype notes) to a tri2∆ (J968) to generate W3991, from which no strains were recorded in the database. W3991-11C, which was just described as MATa in Bob's notes for the W strains book, was crossed to a top1::HIS3 strain (W1956-7C) whose parent diploid contained an sgs1::URA3 allele to generage W4141. Again, no W4141 strains are recorded in the database, but a W4141-44A segregant (MATa top1::HIS3 rDNA::ADE2-CAN1) was then crossed to W2638-18C (MATalpha rad5::URA3). This strain has been confirmed to be his, and ura, but be aware that parental strains were top1, so this strain should probably be backcrossed a few times and the "tri2" = UAF30 locus should be checked, or the original CCFY100 should be backcrossed.
